parts.text: What do you know about Alice?

Alice is a character who experiences various adventures, which are later revealed to be a dream. She interacts with figures such as the White Rabbit, the King, the Queen, and a Fawn. During her experiences, she questions her identity, grows large, and can be both outspoken, as when she tells the Queen she is "nothing but a pack of cards," and timid. She also upsets a jury-box and cries a large pool of tears.
What do you know about Alice?

Alice is a character who experiences various unusual adventures, often questioning her identity during her journey. She interacts with characters such as the White Rabbit, the King, and the Queen. During a trial, she accidentally tips over the jury-box and later argues with the Queen. She also finds herself in a wood where things have no names and meets a Fawn. At one point, she cries so much that she creates a large pool of tears. Many of her experiences turn out to be part of a "curious dream" from which she awakens to her sister.
How did Alice get to Wonderland?
Alice entered Wonderland by following a White Rabbit with pink eyes down a large rabbit-hole. She was curious after seeing the Rabbit take a watch out of its waistcoat-pocket and hurried after it.
Alice went into an open field, a wood, and was in a hall and a pool of tears. She also looked through into a garden and made a survey of the country she was going to travel through.
Alice fell down the rabbit-hole after something, and the rabbit-hole dipped so suddenly that she had no time to stop herself. She then found herself falling down a very deep well.
